full_text: Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 751 Filed 08/10/22 Page 110 of 261 1271 LC6Cmax3 Kate - cross 1 Q. Now, in connection with the claim that you made beginning after you testified in this courthouse following Jeffrey Epstein's death, you sought compensation for therapeutic services; correct? 2 A. Yes. 3 Q. And in connection with your assistance with the government, the FBI victim services awarded you money so that you could seek therapy; correct? 4 A. I'm not sure what it was in connection with. 5 Q. Well, do you doubt that you received money for therapy? 6 A. No, I did. Well, I didn't receive the money, the therapist received the money. 7 Q. Okay. But your therapy was paid for by the government; correct? 8 A. Yes. 9 Q. And you had been in email contact with one of the FBI victim services liaison, both in New York and California; correct? 10 A. Possibly, yes. 11 Q. In fact, they sent you a victim's form to fill out; correct? 12 A. Yes. 13 Q. And you commented on issues concerning the form that they were somewhat complicated. Do you remember that? 14 A. Yes. SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300 DOJ-OGR-00012861
